I've been noticing something odd the past few weeks.  I swear I do better without stat buffs than with them.  I'm not talking hitpoint and a/c buffs, but buff like DEX and STR.

I'm a Rogue so I love getting the Shammy buffs.  When fully buffed I'm maxed out at 255 on both STR and DEX.
My normal STR and DEX are 236 and 216.

Now you'd think that with the maxed STR and DEX I'd be doing noticibley higher and more consistent damage.

Exactly the opposite is true.  When I am fully buffed I have more misses and less powerfull backstabs.  As soon as the buffs wear off, my damage and accuracy improve.  

What the heck?  Anyone else notice this.  At first I thought maybe I was just interpreting things wrong, because I wasn't really watching the damage window that closely.  But last night I made it a point to pay attention to what was happening, and there was a very noticible change.

